  "text": "• angle. The core is Ytterbium dobed and the pump absorption is 18 dB/m. Resonant high index DMF elements are placed in the inner cladding effectively coupling with the HOM ensuring single mode (SM) operation of this very LMA fiber design. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] The DMF rod fiber is resilient to large thermal loads due to these resonant inclusions. The thermo-optic effect is a non local effect that cause the entire rod fiber to heat up when operated at high average power. The heat load gradient perturbs the waveguiding properties increasing the effective refractive index. The core's and also the DMF element's refractive index increases, and ensure SM operation even for large heat loads at high average power levels, where standard PCF fibers become multi mode (MM).",
